jproductioncritic.errorcheckers

Class ErrorChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • jproductioncritic.errorcheckers.ErrorChecker
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DCBias, DigitalClipping, Duration, EditClick, EncodingQuality, GroundLoopHum, InstantaneousNoise, InsufficientDynamicRange, InsufficientDynamicRangeCompression, InsufficientVarietyInDynamics, IsNotStereo, LongSilence, NarrowbandNoise, Phasing, StereoChannelBalance, StereoChannelSimilarity

    public abstract class ErrorChecker
extends java.lang.Object
    This abstract class serves as the superclass of algorithms that check for production errors. Note that extending classes must implement a constructor, which must set all fields to default values, and which must then replace some or all field values with any values that are specified in a ConfigurationSettings object supplied as a parameter to the constructor. Note also that the main processing work will be done in the checkForErrors method.
    Author:
    Cory McKay

      • getErrorReportsMergedAcrossChannels

        protected static java.util.ArrayList<ErrorReport> getErrorReportsMergedAcrossChannels(java.util.ArrayList<ErrorReport>[] separated_reports)
        Returns the given ErrorReports joined into a single set of ErrorReports. If the reported errors are instantaneous, then reports that occur at the same instant are merged. If the reported errors span some time, then reports are merged if they overlap at all. Returned ErrorReports are all sorted by start time. Note that the original sets of error reports are not changed.
        Parameters:
        separated_reports - The ArrayList of ErrorReport objects to merge if appropriate. The array index indicates the audio channel that the reports correspond to. The ArrayList for each channel may not be null, but may be empty. This array must also not be null.
        Returns:
        A set of ErrorReports containing the reports in separated_reports merged across channels.

      • getDefaultConfigurationSettings

        public abstract java.lang.String[][] getDefaultConfigurationSettings()
        Returns the default configuration settings associated with this ErrorChecker for use in creating a default configuration file. This includes the should_check_by_default field inherited from ErrorChecker, but not the title or is_instantaneous fields.
        Returns:
        An array of arrays where the first index corresponds to the individual setting. The second index stores a given setting's configuration key in its 0th entry, and the setting's configuration value in its 1st entry. Returns null if there are no settings. Note that neither keys nor values may include whitespace characters.

      • validateConfigurationSettings

        public abstract void validateConfigurationSettings(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> problems)
        Verify that the configuration settings stored in the fields of this ErrorChecker are set to permitted values, and add an informative report to the given list of problems if they are invalid. Do nothing if the configuration settings stored in the fields are in fact valid.
        Parameters:
        problems - A list of configuration settings problems to add to if there are any problems with the configuration settings values stored in the fields of this ErrorChecker.

      • checkForErrors

        public abstract java.util.ArrayList<ErrorReport> checkForErrors(mckay.utilities.sound.sampled.AudioSamples audio)
                                                         throws java.lang.Exception
        Check the given audio for the technical recording or production error associated with this class and return any detected errors in the form of ErrorReports.
        Parameters:
        audio - The low-level audio data parsed from an audio file that is to be checked. May not be null. It is assumed that all channels in audio contain an equal number of samples.
        Returns:
        All detected errors, sorted by start time and all of the same type. An empty ArrayList is returned if none are found. Will NOT be null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throws an informative exception if error checking cannot be performed.
